Title: AtariTexte
Comments: [a b4ddbec7] Prototype or beta. French language version of AtariWriter - ROM layout is wildly different, also doesn't contain any joystick-checking routines. Supports French character set (even on a 400/800) and French keyboard layout (eg. Numbers written with Shift). When deleting to EOF (Select+BkSp), it asks “Suppres Jusqu'a la Fichier, O/N ?” (“Delete to file, Y/N ?”). (Original English cartridge asks “DELETE TO EOF - ARE YOU SURE, Y/N ?”) Supported printers: 1020, 1025, 1027, Epson FX-80.

Title: AtariTexte

Title: Robotron: 2084
Comments: [m 528fc44a][b][cr] Changes in this image show that it was cut from an earlier file-based crack. In order to disable copy-protection, two 3-byte fragments got changed; they cause the CPU to jump to an address that lies outside of ROM area (the file version could contain such additional code). In effect, this version restarts whenever the player collects either member of the family during gameplay.
